Preparation of lead telluride film and nanometer powder, e.g. for thermoelectric device, involves preparing material by adding lead-containing inorganic substance and tellurium-containing compound into loading solvent

Source e.g. LED for producing light, comprises first and second light-emitting clusters, elements for driving the light-emitting clusters, and a sensing element for sampling a light emitted by the light-emitting clusters
Thermoelectric-generation apparatus has corrosion-coating layer made of organic-inorganic hybrid ceramics formed in inner surface of pipes comprising metal-carbon

Aluminum-alkali hydroxide recyclable hydrogen generator useful in consuming apparatus e.g. fuel cell, comprises aluminum source, hydroxide source, water source, and reaction chamber to produce hydrogen from aluminum, hydroxide and water

Polycrystalline, electronic device including photovoltaic devices, has epitaxial layer of electronic material comprising indirect bandgap semiconductors such as silicon, direct bandgap semiconductors or multiband semiconductors

Thermoelectric cooler for use in illumination device, has cold end comprising insulated metal oxide film formed and located on side of metal base adjacent to P-type and N-type semiconductor elements and connection circuits

Sleeve reaction chamber system i.e. Peltier-assisted microfabricated reaction chamber, for performing e.g. thermal cycling reaction, has activating unit activating pump to reuse stored heat from reservoir to heat device during heating stage
Simulative device for producing hydrocarbon by organic matter has red copper pressing blocks which are respectively connected with anode and cathode of power source

High volume low pressure spray painting machine for minimizing atmospheric exhaust of volatile organic solvent, has thermoelectric semiconductor for absorbing heat released by radiating unit, and control panel provided in case

Functional composition used for molded products, contains organic latent-heat cold-storage heat material, compound including two or more isocyanate groups, and compound including two or more hydroxyl groups

Polycrystalline electronic device e.g. LED device comprises flexible, annealed metal/alloy substrate with primary/secondary recrystallization texture, buffer layer having crystallographic texture, and epitaxial layer of electronic material

Manufacture of laser ablation fine particles film for magnetic material, involves irradiating laser beam to target having metal and metallic compound and maintained in organic solvent, and evaporating solvent under reduced pressure

Thermoelectric module has upper and lower electrodes having synthetic resin substrates, in which electrodes, thermo-elements, substrates and exposure surface of joining metal are coated with moisture-resistance organic film

Formation of high figure of merit thermoelectric material for thermoelectric conversion system, involves depositing mixture of bismuth nanocrystals, tellurium nanocrystals and void generator material on substrate, heating and treating
Thermoelectric conversion sheet for cold preservation and heat retention of e.g. computer CPU, has solar cell conversion portion for supplying electricity to thermoelectric conversion portion

Producing oriented in organic crystalline film i.e. semiconductor film involves forming on substrate a non-monocrystalline film containing inorganic crystalline particles; and crystallizing non-monocrystalline film by heating

Secondary battery used as power source for portable electronic equipment and motor vehicle, comprises separator having inorganic layer containing inorganic particles in which active sites are modified into non-reactive sites

Gas cooling system for electronic display e.g. LCD, has thermoelectric module for cooling gas within auxiliary gas chamber with electronic components whose surface is in contact with gas propelled by cooling chamber fan
Fiber-based electric apparatus for use in e.g. optical circuit, has electric device that is layered on flexible fiber core

Production of urea from synthetic ammonia combining with waste combustion power generation involves synthesizing dried ammonia gas with carbon dioxide to obtain urea, and circulating heat discharged from reaction

Thermoelectric conversion device, useful to transfer heat between connection points, comprises a thermoelectric conversion material comprising a polythienylenevinylene containing thienylenevinylene units
Skin-contacting treatment device for treating malaise, has thermoelectric cell that generates semiconductor nano-particles which are distributed to organic or inorganic insulator, in preset ratio
